Hello. I am encountering a "circular logic" error on a post-synthesis design. I don't believe there should be any error. This is a minimal example:

```verilog
// test.v
module VCC(output P);
  assign P = 1;
endmodule

module GND(output G);
  assign G = 0;
endmodule

module CARRY2(
  output [1:0] CO,
  input        CI,
  input  [1:0] DI, S
);
  assign CO[0] = S[0] ? CI    : DI[0];
  assign CO[1] = S[1] ? CO[0] : DI[1];
endmodule

module A;
  wire const0;
  wire ci;
  GND GND (
    .G(const0)
  );
  CARRY2 CARRY2 (
    .CO(),

    .CI(ci),
    .DI({const0,const0}),
    .S({const0,const0})
  );
endmodule
```

```bash
verilator --lint-only test.v --top A
```

```
%Error: Internal Error: test.v:15:23: ../V3Gate.cpp:872: Circular logic should have been rejected by okVisitor
   15 |   assign CO[0] = S[0] ? CI    : DI[0];
      |                       ^
```

Thanks! I can try taking a look soon

